\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,L)=(1-\epsilon,\alpha)$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon,\alpha>0$
\end_inset

 small, letting 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\rightarrow0$
\end_inset

 more quickly than 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon\rightarrow0$
\end_inset

 corresponds to taking an arbitry limit in the authorized 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,L)$
\end_inset

-space towards 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,L)=(1,0)$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{{\rm c}}(1-\epsilon)\sim|L_{{\rm c}}(1)|\epsilon$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,\ell)\rightarrow(1,0)$
\end_inset

, meaning that we have
\end_layout

